 Sure, I can help you with that. Here's an example XML file for your mission plan:
```php
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<mission>
    <starting_point>
        <latitude>37.366275</latitude>
        <longitude>-120.4230300</longitude>
    </starting_point>
    <tasks>
        <task id="1">
            <name>Find a tree in the middle of the orchard and measure cos.</name>
            <location>
                <latitude>37.366275</latitude>
                <longitude>-120.4230300</longitude>
            </location>
        </task>
        <task id="2">
            <name>Take 2 pictures of nearby trees.</name>
            <location>
                <latitude>37.366275</latitude>
                <longitude>-120.4230300</longitude>
            </location>
        </task>
        <task id="3">
            <name>Measure another tree as far away as possible for co2.</name>
            <location>
                <latitude>37.366275</latitude>
                <longitude>-120.4230300</longitude>
            </location>
        </task>
        <task id="4">
            <name>Repeat the same process.</name>
            <location>
                <latitude>37.366275</latitude>
                <longitude>-120.4230300</longitude>
            </location>
        </task>
        <task id="5">
            <name>Take a temperature reading at any one of the northern most trees.</name>
            <location>
                <latitude>37.366289</latitude>
                <longitude>-120.4230141</longitude>
            </location>
        </task>
    </tasks>
    <end_point>
        <latitude>37.366289</latitude>
        <longitude>-120.4230141</longitude>
    </end_point>
</mission>
```
This XML file defines a mission with a starting point, a list of tasks to be performed, and an end point. Each task has a unique ID, a name describing the task, and a location specifying the latitude and longitude coordinates of the task. The end point is also specified by its latitude and longitude coordinates.

You can modify this XML file to include additional tasks or change the locations as needed for your mission plan. 